commit.message: Fix psimd_qfma_f32 for FMA-enabled x86 processors
Default to not use QFMA instructions on WAsm SIMD

Require signed mask in blend of unsigned SIMD vectors

The result of comparison of unsigned SIMD vectors is a signed SIMD vector.
Using it as a mask with previous specification was incompatible with gcc.
Optimized blends and FP32 min/max for WAsm SIMD128

psimd_load_splat_* functions

New psimd_load_splat_[u8/s8/u16/s16/u32/s32/f32] functions load a single value and duplicate it to all lanes
Add concat even/odd functions for 8-bit types
Recognize both __ARM_NEON__ and __ARM_NEON as NEON macros
New API for vector shuffles + additional shuffle operations
Make header compatible with recent Apple Clang
